    <h1 style="text-align:center; padding-bottom:30px;">How to find a job in Melbourne？</h1>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6" style="padding-right: 1px;
    padding-left: 1px">
            <img src="/images/findjob.png" style="width:100%; height:100%">
        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-6" style="padding-right: 1px;
            padding-left: 1px">
            <div class="card" style="width: 100%;">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title" style="margin-top:5%">1 Finding a job through a network of relationships</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Most jobs are never advertised in Australia, and you can only get a job through building a network. This considerable job vacancy has also formed a so-called invisible labor market. In this kind of employment environment, it is essential to get along with everyone and establish their new connections.
                    </p>
                    <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted" style="font-size: 0.6em">Tip: Pay attention to their communication style, and what types of communications they say "yes" to most often. </h6>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card" style="width: 100%;">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title" style="margin-top:5%">2 Start from the volunteering contact the Australian workplace</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Many new immigrants cannot find work because they do not have local work experience. It is recommended to participate in volunteers in some organizations or communities with time and energy.
                        This type of work does not require too much of the applicant's professional qualifications or work experience but must have the enthusiasm to help others. During volunteering, you can learn English, become familiar with local culture, and get valuable referral resources.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
